management

Class Module

  • java.lang.Object
    • management.Module

  • public class Module
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the representation of a single Module.

    Several constructors assure the usability for several use cases.

    Entries are used to build modules and fill them with content. A list of modules with additional data represents a complete document. Entries can be following extensions of the Entry class: CourseEntry, EffortEntry, TextualEntry.

    Author:
    AJ, add names here...
    See Also:
    Entry, CourseEntry, EffortEntry, TextualEntry, SelfStudy
